# Linting and type checking

This project uses ruff for linting and formatting, and mypy for type checking.
Generated code must pass both without errors.

Key ruff settings:

- Line length: 100
- Enabled rule sets: E4/E7/E9, F, I, UP, B, SIM, C4, PIE, RUF, ANN, NPY, PD
- `src/` functions must have type annotations on all arguments and return values
- `tests/` are exempt from annotation rules if configured that way in pyproject
- `notebooks/` are exempt from ANN and common notebook false positives

Key mypy settings:

- `check_untyped_defs = true` - untyped functions are still checked internally
- `ignore_missing_imports = true` - DS libraries with missing stubs will not cause errors

RULE: All code in `src/` must pass `ruff check` and `mypy` without errors.
RULE: Do not add `# type: ignore` or `# noqa` comments unless there is a genuine false positive - fix the code instead.

<!-- project-template:extension:agent-linting:start -->
RULE: Do not add type annotations to marimo cell functions; notebooks are not type-checked.
<!-- project-template:extension:agent-linting:end -->

