Downstream templates should append specialised rules in this section.
Keep the generic base rules above unless a downstream project has a clear
reason to override them.

<!-- project-template:extension:downstream-rules:start -->
RULE: When given a business question or analytical goal, invoke the ds-workflow
skill before generating code.
RULE: For every stage that produces a notebook, the marimo skill applies.
RULE: For every stage that produces figures, the ds-visualisation skill applies
and all mandatory figures must be saved to `FIGURES_DIR`.
RULE: Every analytical task must produce reusable functions in `src/` organised
by responsibility.
RULE: Every analytical task must produce pytest tests covering reusable `src/`
functions.
RULE: Scripts orchestrate pipelines by calling `src/` functions; they do not
implement analytical logic directly.
RULE: All dataframe operations should use Polars. Pandas may be used only when
required by an external library, and conversions should happen at the call site.
RULE: Reports are named `YYYY-MM-DD_<activity>.md`.
RULE: Figures are named `<subject>_<chart_type>.png`.
